1
00:00:03,513 --> 00:00:09,685
We want to get to the point, where 
the person, the gamer, is the movie.

2
00:00:09,838 --> 00:00:14,775
Not just first person shooter, 
where you’re in it, you’re in this movie.

3
00:00:14,994 --> 00:00:18,723
[LiveStreaming Reality Images]

4
00:00:18,877 --> 00:00:21,748
And we know,
there are ‘movies’ like that too,

5
00:00:21,748 --> 00:00:25,607
everyone can make a list now 
of what they’ve seen.

6
00:00:25,607 --> 00:00:31,982
But to give all of this some credence, 
is what I mean to say, when …

7
00:00:32,841 --> 00:00:38,267
Let’s start with Sukadev Goswami 
or let’s leap to him.

8
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:43,050
pariniṣṭhito ’pi nairguṇya
uttama-śloka-līlayā 
[SB: 2.1.9]

9
00:00:43,050 --> 00:00:46,973
He’s saying,
“I wasn’t watching any movies.

10
00:00:47,188 --> 00:00:51,420
I’ve never seen any movies.
I was in the nirguna plane.”

11
00:00:51,420 --> 00:00:55,275
Remember, he was liberated
in the womb of his mother,

12
00:00:55,275 --> 00:00:59,745
and also rather large, 
not just a little baby,

13
00:00:59,745 --> 00:01:03,642
but he came out 
fully developed, liberated.

14
00:01:03,642 --> 00:01:06,175
So this is why he’s the speaker 
of the Bhagavatam,

15
00:01:06,175 --> 00:01:09,776
he was never under the influence
of the mundane.

16
00:01:09,776 --> 00:01:17,522
But still, he’s on the outskirts
of the Vaikuntha world, nirguna.

17
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:21,109
“Dive deep into Reality”—
so what does he say?

18
00:01:21,109 --> 00:01:24,752
uttama-śloka-līlayā 
gṛhīta-cetā rājarṣe

19
00:01:24,752 --> 00:01:27,904
ākhyānaṁ yad adhītavān 
[SB: 2.1.9]

20
00:01:27,904 --> 00:01:30,862
But then 
the uttama sloka lila,

21
00:01:30,862 --> 00:01:36,993
“I heard the poetic descriptions
of Krishna.”

22
00:01:36,993 --> 00:01:42,653
That means divine imagery—
divya chaksu—divine vision.

23
00:01:42,653 --> 00:01:44,876
Deeper vision was awakened.

24
00:01:44,876 --> 00:01:49,709
There’s generic divine vision too, 
but deep …

25
00:01:49,709 --> 00:01:54,611
I like to quote Yeats because he said,
“In the deep heart’s core”,

26
00:01:54,611 --> 00:01:58,271
and the Spanish word ‘corazon’
for ‘heart’,

27
00:01:58,271 --> 00:02:02,329
and ‘core’, I like that
because it’s talking about the core.

28
00:02:02,329 --> 00:02:05,253
Because, say, everything has gradation 
according to Guru Maharaj,

29
00:02:05,253 --> 00:02:08,803
so even the heart, 
the outskirts of the heart,

30
00:02:08,803 --> 00:02:12,265
going deeper, then
the deep heart’s core.

31
00:02:12,265 --> 00:02:14,652
So what does Sukadev say?

32
00:02:14,652 --> 00:02:18,753
“When I heard 
these descriptions of Krishna …”

33
00:02:18,753 --> 00:02:23,974
He was flooded with
realtime divine imagery,

34
00:02:25,143 --> 00:02:28,684
not just images
but images of Reality,

35
00:02:28,684 --> 00:02:31,564
Reality images, 
livestreaming Reality images,

36
00:02:31,564 --> 00:02:35,331
and he said, “… which surrounded, 
enveloped my consciousness

37
00:02:35,331 --> 00:02:38,878
and carried me away 
to a domain

38
00:02:38,878 --> 00:02:41,391
that I didn’t know 
existed previously.”

